    {
      "id": "J7sS_x1F7P7DtAfBeYfjf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2870.1527794101953,
      "y": -563.8499611587276,
      "width": 1013.4230160938173,
      "height": 38.70987322173326,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1979440319,
      "version": 1771,
      "versionNonce": 1424108177,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772773936830,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "So at least, Instead of calculating 33 points of data, using appropriate buckets we can reduce it to 5 points of data. \nWe need to resolve the second challenge though to use this solution.",
      "fontSize": 15.483949288693307,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "So at least, Instead of calculating 33 points of data, using appropriate buckets we can reduce it to 5 points of data. \nWe need to resolve the second challenge though to use this solution.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "clKZUGx3szlMg3ee14-aw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4386.130636625451,
      "y": -1254.8197979535066,
      "width": 1166.7140195453546,
      "height": 77.41974644346652,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9l",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 553643231,
      "version": 2054,
      "versionNonce": 26755839,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772773936830,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For the DynamoDB, We can consider a single field `traceroute_object` as it is now. Although, We need to make couple of changes.\n\n    - Create a special logic for aggregation in Artifacts just for traceroute to parse json, calculate aggregation, and store.\n    - For larger buckets, we need to store an array of objects in case of route change. We should create this in the same implementation.",
      "fontSize": 15.483949288693305,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For the DynamoDB, We can consider a single field `traceroute_object` as it is now. Although, We need to make couple of changes.\n\n    - Create a special logic for aggregation in Artifacts just for traceroute to parse json, calculate aggregation, and store.\n    - For larger buckets, we need to store an array of objects in case of route change. We should create this in the same implementation.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WGAtk8h_LiOLml-GZknaB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4382.228066373969,
      "y": -1308.1014229530942,
      "width": 276.77559353539283,
      "height": 24.19367076358329,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#da77f2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9m",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1296890111,
      "version": 1189,
      "versionNonce": 893431921,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772773936830,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Solution 1 (My Preference)",
      "fontSize": 19.35493661086663,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Solution 1 (My Preference)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PMcaAD9pclTaZm94SyEmM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4384.2532734774395,
      "y": -1077.5328943921995,
      "width": 987.8745942739998,
      "height": 174.1944294977997,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9n",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1617133855,
      "version": 2863,
      "versionNonce": 1085639455,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772773936830,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For the DynamoDB, We need to add a new GSI. \n\n    - With GSI, we are able to get all traceroutes data for a single agent.\n    - PK also consist of agent, destination, and also traceroute IDs.\n\nAfter this change in our table\n\n    - We need to be able to map the JSON object of traceroute to DynamoDB items and vice versa.\n    - Any new traceroute is in a separate item. Need to read all of them for the request and create a single object.",
      "fontSize": 15.483949288693307,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For the DynamoDB, We need to add a new GSI. \n\n    - With GSI, we are able to get all traceroutes data for a single agent.\n    - PK also consist of agent, destination, and also traceroute IDs.\n\nAfter this change in our table\n\n    - We need to be able to map the JSON object of traceroute to DynamoDB items and vice versa.\n    - Any new traceroute is in a separate item. Need to read all of them for the request and create a single object.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
